283
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,500
Before His Majesty could say anything,

284
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:19,000
Zhang Lin, the censor, reprimanded him, and rebuked him for his impoliteness.

285
00:17:19,276 --> 00:17:21,267
Prince Dun is always reckless.

286
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:24,800
He has always despised the civil officers and scholars.

287
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:28,200
A censor always gives advice to the Emperor,

288
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:29,900
and points out the wrong-doings of officers.

289
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:33,700
Only they would dare to accuse Prince Dun without mercy.

290
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:36,900
Yes, you're right. Prince Dun didn't do anything then.

291
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,800
But on the way back,

292
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:42,200
